Ajay Agarwal: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 3:59 PM ET
Internet Software and Services

Company Overview of Rave Wireless, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Ajay   Agarwal  Managing Director and Director, Rave Wireless, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 13 Board Members in 13 different organizations across 17 different industries.See Board Relationships----
Background

		Mr. Ajay Agarwal serves as a Managing Director at Bain Capital Ventures, Bain Capital Venture Fund 2007, L.P., Bain Capital Venture Fund 2005, L.P. and Bain Capital Venture Fund, L.P. Mr. Agarwal leads the west coast office and focuses on early stage application software, mobile, software, internet and SaaS investing. At Bain, he is working with early-stage founders on team-building, culture, iteration of product market fit and scaling the early go-to-market operations. ... Mr. Agarwal serves as a Managing Director of Rave Wireless, Inc. He has been an Entrepreneur-in-Residence at Harvard Business School since 2013, where he joined in 2003 and advises MBA students interested in starting companies and works with faculty on research and course development. He served at Versata Software, Inc. He served for over seven years as a Senior Executive at Trilogy Software, Inc. He served as the Head of Sales and Marketing at Trilogy Software, where he grew its annual revenues to $300 million and led Trilogy's product expansion into new vertical markets such as financial services, consumer durables, enterprise pricing and enterprise incentive management. He served as a Consultant of McKinsey & Company, Inc. He is a Director of ShipBob,Inc. He serves as the Chairman of BUILD National Board. He serves on several community boards including Children's Hospital Boston Board of Overseers. He has been a Director of FourKites, Inc. since October 12, 2016. Mr. Agarwal serves as a Director of InfoScout, Inc., Gainsight, Inc., Amazon Robotics LLC, BloomReach, Inc., VMLogix, Inc., and Rave Wireless, Inc. He has been a Director at Kiva Systems LLC (alternate name, Kiva Systems, Inc.) since November 2004, aPriori Technologies, Inc. since March 7, 2005, Skyhook Wireless, Inc. since December 5, 2005, INRIX, Inc. since May 23, 2006 and TellApart, Inc. since June 13, 2011. He has been a Director of Clari Inc. since June 17, 2014. He served as a Director at ThumbPlay Ringtones, LLC since October 30, 2006. He served as a Director of AdReady Inc. and m-Qube, Inc. He served as a Director of Jott Networks, Inc. since May 11, 2007 and Memento, Inc. since April 14, 2005. He served as a Member of Advisory Board at WhisperWire Inc. In 2012 and 2013, he was named to the Forbes Midas list of Tech's Top 100 Investors. He holds a patent for the 'Method and Apparatus of Configuration Solutions'. Mr. Agarwal received an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School in 1995 and a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from Stanford University in 1991.Read Full Background




